# Changelog

All notable changes to this project will be documented in this file.

The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.0.0/), and this project adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html).

## [Unreleased]

---

## [1.0.1] - 2025-08-10

### Changed
- Configuration file setup now copies `config.txt` from the script's source directory instead of generating it. This makes the project more repository-friendly and ensures the default config is version-controlled.

### Fixed
- Corrected dependency check to include `cp` and `dirname`.

---

## [1.0.0] - 2025-08-10

### Added
- Initial release of **Flicker**.
- Core functionality for randomizing wireless TX power at unpredictable intervals.
- Advanced mode (`-A`, `--advanced`) to randomize the `Coverage Class` for MAC-layer timing obfuscation.
- Support for a persistent configuration file at `/etc/flicker/config.txt`.
- Full command-line argument parsing to override all major settings.
- Robust, POSIX-compliant random number generation using `awk`.
- Graceful cleanup routine to restore original wireless settings on exit (`Ctrl+C`).
- Detailed help menu (`-h`, `--help`).
- Logging to `/var/log/flicker.log`.
